  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ 395°F/ Gas 6</p>\n<p>Peel and chop the <strong>sweet potato<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong> into bite-sized pieces</p>\n<p>Add the <strong>butternut squash cubes</strong> and chopped <strong>sweet potato</strong> to a baking tray with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p>\n<p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray in the oven for 15-20 min or until tender and golden</p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/winter-squash-sweet-potato-gratin/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the vegetables are cooking, peel and finely slice the <strong>red onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\n<p>Peel and finely slice the <strong>garlic </strong></p>\n<p>Strip the <strong>sage leaves</strong> from their stalks and chop them finely, discard the stalks</p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/winter-squash-sweet-potato-gratin/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p>\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until softened</p>\n<p>Once softened, add the <strong>chopped sage</strong> and <strong>half</strong> the <strong>sliced garlic</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until fragrant</p>\n<p>Boil a kettle</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/winter-squash-sweet-potato-gratin/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add 30g <span class=\"text-danger\">[60g] </span><strong>butter</strong> with 30g <span class=\"text-danger\">[60g]</span> <strong>flour</strong> to the pan with the<strong> </strong>onion and stir with a wooden spoon for 3-4 min or until the butter melts and a sandy paste forms – this is your <strong>roux</strong></p>\n<p>Gradually whisk 250ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[450ml]</span> <strong>milk</strong> into the roux, a little at a time and cook for 5 min or until a smooth, thick sauce remains</p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/winter-squash-sweet-potato-gratin/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dissolve 1/2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span> <strong>Knorr</strong> <strong>vegetable stock cube</strong> in 50ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[80ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p>\n<p>Add the <strong>Dijon mustard,</strong> <strong>double cream</strong> and <strong>vegetable stock</strong> to the sauce with the <strong>roasted vegetables</strong> </p>\n<p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>gratin</strong></p>\n<p>Transfer the <strong>gratin</strong> to an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong> (or individual ones)</p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/winter-squash-sweet-potato-gratin/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Crush the <strong>hazelnuts </strong>in their bag with a <strong>rolling pin</strong></p>\n<p>Mix the <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong>, <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong> and <strong>crushed hazelnuts</strong> in a bowl – this is your <strong>hazelnut crumb</strong></p>\n<p>Top the <strong>gratin</strong> with the <strong>hazelnut crumb</strong> and put the dish<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span> into the oven for 12–15 min or until golden and bubbling - this is your <strong>winter squash &amp; sweet potato gratin</strong> </p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/winter-squash-sweet-potato-gratin/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, strip the <strong>cavolo nero</strong> leaves from their stalks and tear into bite-sized pieces</p>\n<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p>\n<p>Add the <strong>cavolo nero </strong>with the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>garlic</strong> and a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> </p>\n<p>Cook for 4-5 min or until wilted and softened</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/winter-squash-sweet-potato-gratin/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>winter squash &amp; sweet potato gratin </strong>with the <strong>garlicky cavolo nero</strong> to the side</p>\n<p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
